properties.ground: Willows Oval and Fellows Oval, ANU
properties.desc: The ANU Women’s Football Club is the first and oldest women’s football club established in Canberra. The club’s values revolve around creating a supportive environment for coaches and players, having a community focus, inclusivity, and sports(wo)manship.

Belconnen United Football Club, also known by the name Blue Devils, is a premier League Football Club for men and women. The clubs values are clear in the acronym PRIDE (Passion, Respect, Integrity, Dedication, Excellence).

BellaMonaro Women’s Football Club was established in 2021 specifically for girls and women. The club values friendship, fun, endurance, strength, perseverance, passion, support, success, unity integrity, vision, leadership, trust, commitment and teamwork.
Belnorth Football Club is a community football club that focuses on supporting boys and girls of all ages to gain football skills and a passion for the game.
Belsouth Football Club was previously known as Belsouth Junior Soccer Club. The club aims to ensure that all children playing football are enjoying the game and participating.
Belwest Foxes Soccer Club is a community based club that is run by volunteers. The club has teams playing at both junior and senior level.
The Brindabella Blues Football Club was previously known as The Blue Light Soccer Club. The club aims to create an encouraging learning environment for players, as well as foster a love for the game.

Burns football club is the oldest living football club in the Canberra region. In 1926 when the Federal Capital Territory Soccer Football Association was formed the club began by playing in various local competitions. Originally based in the suburb Forrest, the club re-located to Kambah in 1992. The clubs teams have always played with enthusiasm, passion, and pride.

Canberra Croatia Football club was first established in the 1950s by the Croatian community, who sought to creäte a place where their community could play sport and socialise. At the time it was known as Croatia Soccer club, or Croatia. The club has seen many trophy and premiership successes.
Canberra Olympic presently has men’s and women’s teams that participate in the National Premier League.

Canberra United Football Club was one of the foundation members of the A-league women’s team since its establishment in 2008. A-league women was formerly known as Westfield W-league football from 2008-2021. It is one of Australia’s top women’s football competitions.
Gungahlin United Football Club is one of the largest football clubs in Canberra and Australia. Previously it was known as Gungahlin Soccer Club and Gungahlin Junior Soccer Club.
Lanyon United Football club is a community based club that is inclusive of senior players with all abilities. The club is focused on fun, football, and friendship.
Majura Football Club is a community based club that is largely run by volunteers. The club values participation and inclusiveness.
Monaro Panthers Football Club is a club for all abilities and ages. It is a premier league football club that is friendly, passionate, positive, and professional.
O’Connor Knights Football club is a community based non-profit club that was founded by the Croatian community and is largely run by many volunteers.
Queanbeyan City Football Club is a community based non-profit football club. The club’s values revolve around fair play, fun, and participation. The club puts emphasis on fun and learning.

South Canberra Football Club was established in 2021 as a women’s football club. The club was founded by Kat Yulie and Emma Steel. It has a strong focus on female empowerment. Compared to mixed-gender clubs, this football establishment focuses specifically on the women’s game. Although it is not the first women’s football club to be established, it has very specific club culture and values. Some of the club’s ideals surround mental health and social connection. It’s core values are teamwork, respect, fun, inclusion, and community. South Canberra Football Club creates strength, conditioning, and exercise programs specifically for women’s football training in the club. The club encourages diversity and equality. It was established after a rise in the number of girls who play football.

In 1976 Kambah United Soccer club played its first season. The club later merged with Tuggeranong soccer club (formerly known as Wanniassa Soccer Club) in 1986 to form Tuggeranong United. The club welcomes players of all ages, genders, and skill levels.
The UC Stars Football club was originally established under the name UC Puma’s. The club fosters a fun, inclusive and competitive environment to play football and connect with others.

West Canberra Wanderers Football Club was formerly known as Woden-West Football Club. The club provides a pathway for players into the National Premier League. It has teams in all divisions of the NPL. The magpie that is depicted on the club’s logo is a well-known songbird in Western Canberra recognised for it’s attacking intent.
Weston Molonglo Football Club was initially known as Weston Creek Soccer Club. It was established as an all-age club.

The values of Woden Valley Soccer Club are excellence, integrity, accountability, respect, community, fun, and teamwork. The club welcomes people with all abilities and ages. In 1996 the club introduced and integrated the game of football for girls joining the club.
